IT Budget




HGST (formerly Hitachi Global Storage Technologies provides computer hard drive systems to businesses and private consumers.  HGST was acquired by Western Digital in 2012 from Hitachi America, Ltd.  HGST now operates as an independent subsidiary of Western Digital.  Western Digital… MoreHGST (formerly Hitachi Global Storage Technologies provides computer hard drive systems to businesses and private consumers.  HGST was acquired by Western Digital in 2012 from Hitachi America, Ltd.  HGST now operates as an independent subsidiary of Western Digital.  Western Digital acquired and integrated sTec, Inc. into HGST in late 2013.

Western Digital is integrating significant portions of HGST staff and systems.
HGST (formerly Hitachi Global Storage Technologies provides computer hard drive systems to businesses and private consumers.  HGST was acquired by Western Digital in 2012 from Hitachi America, Ltd.  HGST now operates as an independent subsidiary of Western Digital.  Western Digital… MoreHGST (formerly Hitachi Global Storage Technologies provides computer hard drive systems to businesses and private consumers.  HGST was acquired by Western Digital in 2012 from Hitachi America, Ltd.  HGST now operates as an independent subsidiary of Western Digital.  Western Digital acquired and integrated sTec, Inc. into HGST in late 2013.

HGST's IT department is based in San Jose, CA, and consists of teams dealing with IT needs specific to HGST. The IT executive office is supported by the Enterprise Technology group, which assists with internal IT as well as product development for the company.

Teams working directly for HGST handle the enterprise's applications management and business intelligence.

Additionally, there are offices dealing with infrastructure services, customer service management, security, and business operations.
 





